00:44:07.420 --> 00:44:10.320
-A distant star is
orbited by two planets.

00:44:10.320 --> 00:44:14.450
One looks similar to the Earth--
the other is a gas giant.

00:44:14.450 --> 00:44:16.840
When viewed from a
distance, the two planets

00:44:16.840 --> 00:44:19.620
disappear into the
glare of their sun.

00:44:19.620 --> 00:44:22.080
How could we ever find
these planets all the way

00:44:22.080 --> 00:44:23.470
from the Earth?

00:44:23.470 --> 00:44:26.260
By using a space telescope
with a coronagraph

00:44:26.260 --> 00:44:30.080
to separate starlight
from planet light.

00:44:30.080 --> 00:44:32.550
As the star's light passes
through the telescope's

00:44:32.550 --> 00:44:36.030
large mirrors, it picks
up small distortions.

00:44:36.030 --> 00:44:40.090
Diffraction adds concentric
rings to the image we see.

00:44:40.090 --> 00:44:42.740
To reveal the planets,
first, the coronagraph

00:44:42.740 --> 00:44:45.590
uses a mask to block
much of the star's light

00:44:45.590 --> 00:44:49.350
and redirect the remaining
light to the outer edges.

00:44:49.350 --> 00:44:51.420
A washer-shaped
device can now block

00:44:51.420 --> 00:44:54.650
most of the rest of
the star's light.

00:44:54.650 --> 00:44:57.580
Because the planet's light
comes in at an angle,

00:44:57.580 --> 00:45:00.480
it misses the mask and
passes through the center

00:45:00.480 --> 00:45:02.410
of the washer.

00:45:02.410 --> 00:45:03.960
But when we turn
up the image signal

00:45:03.960 --> 00:45:06.150
by collecting more
light, we can see

00:45:06.150 --> 00:45:08.750
that the planets are
still hidden under blobs

00:45:08.750 --> 00:45:10.940
of leftover starlight.

00:45:10.940 --> 00:45:13.070
To remove these
blobs, the coronagraph

00:45:13.070 --> 00:45:15.470
has a special
deformable mirror that

00:45:15.470 --> 00:45:19.100
can change shape by using
hundreds of tiny pistons.

00:45:19.100 --> 00:45:22.460
This can correct distortions
in the light beam.

00:45:22.460 --> 00:45:26.360
As the mirror deforms, the blobs
of light as seen in the monitor

00:45:26.360 --> 00:45:30.120
slowly begin disappearing,
finally revealing the brighter

00:45:30.120 --> 00:45:32.200
of the two planets.

00:45:32.200 --> 00:45:36.810
Afterwards, the fainter
planet also comes into view.

00:45:36.810 --> 00:45:40.180
We can now see objects more
than a billion times fainter

00:45:40.180 --> 00:45:42.270
than the star.

00:45:42.270 --> 00:45:43.800
And if the light
from these planets

00:45:43.800 --> 00:45:46.920
is passed through a prism,
we can spread it out

00:45:46.920 --> 00:45:49.560
into rainbows of color.

00:45:49.560 --> 00:45:51.390
But some colors are missing.

00:45:51.390 --> 00:45:55.250
They were absorbed by gases
in each planet's atmosphere,

00:45:55.250 --> 00:45:58.810
giving us important clues
about their composition.

00:45:58.810 --> 00:46:00.760
The search for life
in the universe

00:46:00.760 --> 00:46:02.740
has taken a new step forward.

